metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #205
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)

metadata.name: Bamboo and Beyond #16
metadata.description:
The idea was inspired by Japanese paintings that always express peace and tranquility.

Without using any images and only using programming knowledge, each mint is tried to be a unique and relaxing work of art. “Bamboo and Beyond” is an exploration to find harmony and calm in a work of art with a minimal style. each bamboo has a unique structure that creates a minimal work of art with a variety of color palettes, arrangements and leaves.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: One Tezo Drawings_114+ #11
metadata.description:
The One Tezo Drawings project is a variation of the “Desenhos de um Real” project (2006- ). In it, the artist sets the price of his work by making a rational calculation, equating his artistic production with a consumer good detached from the art world .
In this case, the calculation is based on the amount charged per hour of work from the minimum wage in the United States. Thus, a drawing that took X hours to produce (Wt) will have its price fixed at USD 15.00 * Wt divided by the value in Dollars of one Tezo (Dt) at the time of publication. But for the final price to be 1.00 Tez, the total production time value (Wt) will be divided by the number of editions (Ed). Therefore, the number of editions is defined by the following formula: 1.00 Tez = (Wt*15/Dt)/Ed ==> 

Ed=Wt*15/Dt 

For this particular project:
Permutation of 10 to 16 mirrored layers.

Wt= 9.75
Dt= 2.14
Ed= 9.75*15/2.14 = 68

Press J or P to save a 1500x1500px image
NFT Licence 2.0 - Diego de los Campos

metadata.name: SoulFish #203
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by Zhuāngzǐ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

Interactivities:
> Key S: Save
> Holding mouse in different directions: Swim 
> Click and let the fish touch the Bubbles
> Key B: Toggle border
> Key P: Pause

metadata.description: NeuralFaces is an AI-driven avatar collection based on a neural network that was trained on face sketches. The latent vector for each face is generated from the transaction hash.

metadata.name: Traces #48
metadata.description:
Traces is an exploration around movement.
Inspired but motion blur in photography, using lines travelling through obstacles, it can create scenes, sometimes representation of virtual landscapes.

Its features include:
- A choice between 12 modern and 7 rarer palette inspired by some of my photographies (revealed on my twitter with the first mint
- 3 definitions
- 3 types of obstacles modifying the motion
- Rare symmetrical dispositions

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

Unsold will be burnt after a certain time, and price might increase

metadata.name: Bamboo #33
metadata.description:
During my childhood we had a small patch of bamboo in our backyard. 
I fondly remember playing with the hollow sticks but also cutting myself on the fibrous leaves.
"Bamboo" aims to capture the adventures I would envision while looking at that small jungle in my garden.

Inspiration was drawn from pointillism, botanical illustration and naive art.

The piece is purely generative, in the sense of painting the picture with code via p5js points and shapes, no assets are used.

Generative parameters include density of elements, parameters of elements and color. 

Thank you so much for collecting!

's' to capture a 6400 x 6400 png with border

'b' to capture a 6400 x 6400 png without border

metadata.name: Connected #3
metadata.description:
An artistic version of the travelling salesperson problem.
In this particle system, each particle has to visit a complete set of attractors.
The path of each particle is then plotted, resulting in unique abstract geometries.


Artist: Estienne
Made with p5.js
Dec 2021
